5:
Sorry, Mary. You really are a pain in
the butt.
13:
Well, you are. The fact that you still
expect nothing but nice words from
us speaks volumes.
17:
B-but... Why are you all still choosing
to help me?
20:
I've been so self-centered this whole
time...
32:
Heh-heh. The Felders are used to
dealing with annoying folk who don't
understand themselves.
35:
...Besides, you're, like... my friend. It's
not like I'm gonna leave you high
and dry when you need us most.
40:
I like people like you. You won't give
up no matter how hopeless or
cowardly you are.
42:
So go ahead, keep running in the
opposite direction. I'll come
dragging you the other way as
many times as I need to!
51:
You have the desire to try, so I'll stay
with you for as long as it takes.
55:
I'm going to ask you again, Mary.
What are you running from?
60:
I... I want to tell him, I really do. But...
I'm just so scared...
62:
I'm scared of ruining our friendship
and losing him.
66:
...I don't know if I could survive that.
Will's been there for me since the
very beginning.
71:
...I come from a place surrounded
by nothing but the ocean, but I
drifted into this city alone one day
when I was little.
78:
I was taken in by a couple who
became my parents, and everyone I
met here was kind to me... But I
couldn't forget my old home.
81:
I didn't want to be a burden, so I hid
from everyone how lonely I was.
86:
Did you make this, Wilfred? It's so
cute!
88:
M-Mary... Do you... feel less lonely
now?
99:
...Will told me, "I'm happy that we're
still good friends after all these
years."
101:
I think Will wants to maintain what
we've had since we were little, so I
don't want to risk losing that...
105:
Okay, Little Miss Goody Two-shoes.
That's enough.
113:
You're not telling us how you really
feel, are you? Stop beating around
the bush and tell us what you want.
117:
Again with the bully circle! Can't you
two be a little nicer?
121:
I want to know what you're really
feeling, too.
128:
Just being friends with Will... It's not
enough. I want to be lovers.
130:
The way things are now... It's just not
enough. I want to hold his hand...
Squeeze him close...
133: I... I want to kiss him, too!
137:
...Ever since that day... I've been in
love with him. From the bottom of
my heart, I know I have to try!
142:
Then I guess Operation: Snag the
Childhood Friend 2 is a go.
147:
Yeah, let's do it! Time to channel all
that pain-in-the-butt energy into a
decisive victory!
149:
Believe in yourself, Mary. I know
you're not the type to be satisfied
until you've done everything you
can do!
171:
She's kind and strong, always
helping others... Even people like me.
Not to mention she's the cutest,
most beautiful person ever.
175:
Just being her friend for all these
years is an honor in and of itself! But
still, I...
178:
I love her! I have to tell her I love her!
I can't lie to myself anymore
182: H-hey! Shut up! Please! I'm sorry!
186:
You sure it was a good idea bringing
those things with you? Didn't the
Guild entrust them to you for
research purposes?
190:
I left them back in my lab, but these
things have a mind of their own!
They follow me around, say
whatever they want
194:
Said exactly what you're thinking,
didn't it? Whatever. It's time for you
to make a decision.
198:
...It's already a miracle that I can be
this happy.
200:
But if I tell her how I feel, it's just
going to cause trouble for her... I
can't risk losing our friendship
209:
...I'm sorry to keep bothering you,
Will. But...
213:
U-um... Would you go on another
date with me?
